      <hedline>
        <hl1>The New Look of the Senate Race</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mike Kelly letter on Rick Lazio's opinion that Hillary Clinton's ambition is issue in New York Senate campaign; notes that Lazio is in same position (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Giuliani's Change of Heart'' (column, May 22): Bob Herbert seems to say that because Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani is not a kind person, and because his recent display of humility and of hope that he can reach out to all New Yorkers is belated, the mayor is a failure worthy of our pity, not our sympathy and much less our respect.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Giuliani's Change of Heart'' (column, May 22): Bob Herbert seems to say that because Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani is not a kind person, and because his recent display of humility and of hope that he can reach out to all New Yorkers is belated, the mayor is a failure worthy of our pity, not our sympathy and much less our respect.</p>
        <p>It doesn't seem to matter that Mr. Giuliani has miraculously transformed New York City. To Mr. Herbert, Mr. Giuliani's career ''has been about power and control.'' How does Mr. Herbert know the mayor's motives for improving the quality of our lives? On his record of crime reduction alone, Mayor Giuliani is the kindest mayor New York City has ever had.</p>
        <p>CHARLES G. THOMAS  New York, May 22, 2000</p>
      </block>
